---
import YardageMarker from './YardageMarker.astro';
import { revealClass, sectionClass } from '../lib/ui';
---

<section
  id="the-gap"
  aria-labelledby="reframe-heading"
  class:list={[sectionClass, 'bg-surface']}
>
  <div class="mx-auto max-w-[1200px]">
    <YardageMarker yard="50Y" label="The gap" />

    <div class={revealClass} data-reveal style="--stagger: 40ms;">
      <h2
        id="reframe-heading"
        class="max-w-[11ch] text-[2.4rem] leading-[1.02] font-light tracking-[-0.05em] text-onbackground md:text-[3.15rem] lg:text-[3.6rem]"
      >
        You&apos;ve got the tools. You&apos;re missing the plan.
      </h2>
    </div>

    <div class="mt-8 grid gap-8 md:mt-10 md:grid-cols-2 md:gap-12">
      <p
        class:list={[revealClass, 'text-[1rem] leading-7 text-[var(--body-soft)] md:text-[1.08rem] md:leading-8']}
        data-reveal
        style="--stagger: 120ms;"
      >
        A launch monitor. A swing app. A GPS watch. A stat tracker. And still, when you get to
        the range, you&apos;re standing over a pile of balls trying to remember what your coach said
        and whether to start with driver or wedges.
      </p>
      <p
        class:list={[revealClass, 'text-[1rem] leading-7 text-onbackground md:text-[1.08rem] md:leading-8']}
        data-reveal
        style="--stagger: 220ms;"
      >
        The gap is structure. Rangework fills it. Build your session at home, walk through it on
        the mats, and pick up exactly where you left off if your phone dies or your mate wants to
        chat.
      </p>
    </div>
  </div>
</section>
